    {
      "id": "mem_overlook-veld-006-bridge-token-positive",
      "content": "POSITIVE: Bridge token auth system in Veld is well-designed — SHA-256 hashed, server-validated, session-limited (6 concurrent max), auto-refresh, clean logout with token revocation. This is a counter-example to the other auth findings: when Veld builds auth intentionally (bridge tokens), it's done right. The problem is inconsistency, not incompetence.",
      "type": "Learning",
      "importance": 0.82,
